                "# Real World Use Case: Support Ticket Routing\n",
                "\n",
                "**Scenario**: 10,000 emails come in daily ("My internet is down", "Billing error", "Feature request").\n",
                "**Goal**: Route them to the right team (Tech Support, Finance, Product).\n",
                "**Method**: Fine-tune BERT."
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": null,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "# Conceptual Fine-Tuning Code\n",
                "\n",
                "print(\"1. Load 'bert-base-uncased'\")\n",
                "print(\"2. Replace the 'Head' (the last layer)\")\n",
                "print(\"   Original Head: size 30,000 (Vocabulary)\")\n",
                "print(\"   New Head: size 3 (Tech, Finance, Product)\")\n",
                "print(\"3. Freeze the Body (optional) or Train Everything (low learning rate)\")\n",
                "print(\"4. Feed email -> [CLS] token -> Dense Layer -> Softmax -> 'Finance'\")"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
